TITLE: Hugo Papermod: Conditional Cover Image and Twitter Site Logic
DESCRIPTION: This Go Template snippet manages the display of cover images for a page, checking if a `cover.image` exists and if its path is relative. It also extracts and formats the Twitter site handle from the site parameters, ensuring it starts with an '@' symbol for proper Twitter card meta tag generation.

SOURCE: https://github.com/adityatelange/hugo-papermod/blob/master/layouts/partials/templates/twitter_cards.html#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Go Template
CODE:
```
{{- if .Params.cover.image -}}
  {{- if (ne $.Params.cover.relative true) }}  {{- else }}  {{- end}}
{{- else }}
  {{- $images := partial "templates/_funcs/get-page-images" . -}}
  {{- with index $images 0 -}}   {{- else -}}  {{- end -}}
{{- end }}

{{- $twitterSite := "" }}
{{- with site.Params.social }}
  {{- if reflect.IsMap . }}
    {{- with .twitter }}
      {{- $content := . }}
      {{- if not (strings.HasPrefix . "@") }}
        {{- $content = printf "@%v" . }}
      {{- end }}
    {{- end }}
  {{- end }}
{{- end }}
```

