TITLE: JavaScript: Control Scroll-to-Top Button Visibility
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript function controls the visibility and opacity of a 'scroll-to-top' button (element with ID 'top-link'). The button becomes visible and opaque when the user scrolls down more than 800 pixels from the top of the page, and hidden otherwise, providing a visual cue for easy navigation back to the top.

SOURCE: https://github.com/adityatelange/hugo-papermod/blob/master/layouts/partials/footer.html#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
var mybutton = document.getElementById("top-link");
window.onscroll = function () {
  if (document.body.scrollTop > 800 || document.documentElement.scrollTop > 800) {
    mybutton.style.visibility = "visible";
    mybutton.style.opacity = "1";
  } else {
    mybutton.style.visibility = "hidden";
    mybutton.style.opacity = "0";
  }
};
```

