TITLE: JavaScript: Persist Horizontal Menu Scroll Position
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript code snippet manages the horizontal scroll position of an HTML element with the ID 'menu'. It retrieves the last saved scroll position from `localStorage` on page load and updates it whenever the menu is scrolled, ensuring the user's view is maintained across sessions.

SOURCE: https://github.com/adityatelange/hugo-papermod/blob/master/layouts/partials/footer.html#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
let menu = document.getElementById('menu')
if (menu) {
  menu.scrollLeft = localStorage.getItem("menu-scroll-position");
  menu.onscroll = function () {
    localStorage.setItem("menu-scroll-position", menu.scrollLeft);
  }
}
```

